  "text": "T . It was composed of phosphatidylethanolamine, three unidentified aminolipids (AL1-3), two phospholipids (PL1, PL2), four aminophospholipids (APL1-4) and six lipids without a functional group (L1-6). Furthermore, a yellow pigment spot was visible showing highly hydrophobic chromatographic motility. This polar lipid profile was significantly more complex than that of M. auburnensis but of similar complexity to that of M. phyllosphaerae [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In addition, numerous unidentified lipids reported to be present in M. phyllosphaerae were also found Summed feature 4 ‡ --",
